The Yangtze River Delta (YRD) mainly consists of Shanghai City, Jiangsu Province, and Zhejiang Province. Zhejiang Province includes 11 prefecture-level cities, while Jiangsu Province includes 13 prefecture-level cities (Fig. 1
). The Yangtze River Delta Urban Agglomeration is one of the six largest metropolitan areas in the world and the largest metropolitan area in China (Tian et al., 2011). Urbanization level in the YRD increased from 47.95% in 2000 to 65.09% in 2010 (Fig. 2
). The urbanization level of Shanghai is higher than those of Zhejiang and Jiangsu Provinces. The urbanization level of Jiangsu is the lowest in the YRD, but it has increased quickly. The gap of urbanization level between Jiangsu and Zhejiang has narrowed, and the urbanization level of Jiangsu was equal to that of Zhejiang in 2010.
